# Recipe Extraction API (minimal backend)

This app is static on GitHub Pages, so reliable OCR/vision extraction must run in a backend API.

## Recommended minimal architecture

- Frontend: GitHub Pages (this repo)
- Backend: one serverless endpoint (`POST /api/extract`)
- Model: vision-capable model returning strict JSON
- Security: API key stored only in backend environment secrets

## Suggested deployment

1. Deploy `extract-worker.js` to Cloudflare Workers (or adapt to Vercel/Netlify Functions).
2. Set environment secret `OPENAI_API_KEY`.
3. Copy the deployed endpoint URL.
4. Paste URL in the app's **Extraction API URL** field.

## Request format from frontend

```json
{
  "imageData": "data:image/jpeg;base64,...",
  "filename": "recipe-photo.jpg"
}
```

## Expected response shape

```json
{
  "title": "Recipe title",
  "ingredients": [
    {"section":"Produce","amount":2,"unit":"whole","item":"onions"}
  ],
  "instructions": "Step-by-step text",
  "tags": ["quick"]
}
```

If extraction confidence is low, backend should still return partial fields and empty arrays/strings so frontend can open draft review.
